<TITLE> Pabna mob lynches 4 suspected robbers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, Nov 9 (bdnews24.com) Angry villagers in in Pabna beat four suspected robbers to death early Sunday, police said. "Around ten to twelve armed members of the defunct militant outfit Purbo Banglar Communist Party (Janojuddho) went to bank official Jainal's residence in Hatbarhia village, Santhia upazila, at around three in the morning," Santhia police chief Moniruzzaman told reporters. "The desperate hue and cry of the members of the besieged family roused the villagers. They chased the fleeing suspects and caught five of them. Four were killed on the spot from the beating of the assembled villagers." The deceased were identified as: Ebad Ali, 34, from Bhulbarhia, Robiul, 30, and Lal Hossdain, 30, of Swarbhawanipur and Shamim Hossain, 26, from Tebarhia, in Santhia. Police arrested Hablu, 29, and retrieved two firearms and two rounds of ammunition from the spot, Zaman said. The bodies of the deceased have been sent to the morgue at Pabna Sadar Hospital for autopsy and attempted robbery charges have been filed with Santhia police station. bdnews24
